# ======================================================================
# .gitignore for v1.0.0-ORM-submission
# Public release policy: metadata + coding CSVs + scripts only.
# Primary-source PDFs and full-text extracts are NOT redistributed;
# they are referenced by DOI / URL in the case registry.
# ======================================================================

# System and Python
.DS_Store
*.pyc
__pycache__/
.venv/
*.tmp
.codex/

# Scratch output and logs
10_outputs/
08_logs/

# April 8 rerun scratch (pre-manuscript version; not in the submission release)
11_manuscript_rerun_2026_04_08/

# Primary sources — copyright + green-OA distribution rules differ by source,
# so we release DOIs/URLs (in 01_registry/) but not the PDFs or extracts.
03_raw_sources/
04_extracted_text/
04_extracted_text_cleaned/
00_input/

# Case notes (private researcher annotations; not part of the reproducible coding)
05_case_notes/

# Editorial-loop and review-loop intermediate versions — keep only the
# convergence reports, not every vNN snapshot.
11_manuscript/10_drafts/10_manuscript_versions/editorial_loop/v*.md
11_manuscript/10_drafts/10_manuscript_versions/editorial_loop/v*.docx
11_manuscript/10_drafts/10_manuscript_versions/review_loop/v*.md
11_manuscript/10_drafts/10_manuscript_versions/review_loop/v*.docx

# Codex / internal tool state
.codex/

# Published third-party ORM/SMJ/JoM template PDFs used for editorial design
# reference; copyright-restricted, not redistributable
11_manuscript/30_reviews/template_pdfs/

# Expanded reference library PDFs are OA (arXiv/PMC/author-deposit)
# but vary in redistribution licensing — exclude from public repo,
# document only via STATUS.md and manifest.md
11_manuscript/20_citations/expanded_reference_library/pdfs/

# Modern-replacement PDFs (author deposits; same conservative redistribution policy)
11_manuscript/20_citations/expanded_reference_library/modern_replacements/pdfs/
